						               													<description>Trick and Trade is a &amp;quot;may-follow&amp;quot; trick-taking game themed around cryptocurrency speculation.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are four suits for the 4 competing currencies, and a separate deck of cards which will represent the players' holdings in those currencies.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the end of a trick, the highest ranked card of the lead suit goes to a market area, with the market value of cards being inversely related to their rank. Also at the end of a trick, the players draft, in card strength order, one of the holdings cards from a face up display.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the end of a hand, the players will rank the currency's values based upon the cards from each suit which won tricks, with the most valued being worth 3 points per holding, then 2, then 1, then -1.  The players value their holdings, record their scores, and the player with the most points wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
